<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-84-0949 </DOCNO><TEXT>MRI has enormous potential for evaluating the vascular system. A numberof important clinical uses are already evident, and most are describedin this chapter. Research proceeds to develop the technique in a quantitativedirection in an effort to provide a noninvasive method for measuringflow and perfusion. It is likely that the current uses of MRI in thevascular system represent the tip of the iceberg.</TEXT></DOC>